-letter-spacing);\"><span class=\" fusion-imageframe imageframe-none imageframe-4 hover-type-none\" style=\"border-radius:15px;\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1980\" height=\"1318\" alt=\"Medical Student from Giridhar Eye Hospital\" title=\"Medical Student from Giridhar Eye Hospital\" src=\"https:\/\/www.giridhareye.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/11\/medical-student4-scaled.jpeg\" class=\"img-responsive wp-image-7584\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.giridhareye.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/11\/medical-student4-300x200.jpeg 300w, https:\/\/www.giridhareye.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/11\/medical-student4-scaled.jpeg 1980w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1980px) 100vw, 1980px\" \/><\/span><\/div><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-layout-column fusion_builder_column fusion-builder-column-7 fusion_builder_column_3_5 3_5 fusion-flex-column\" style=\"--awb-bg-size:cover;--awb-width-large:60%;--awb-margin-top-large:0px;--awb-spacing-right-large:3.2%;--awb-margin-bottom-large:20px;--awb-spacing-left-large:3.2%;--awb-width-medium:60%;--awb-order-medium:0;--awb-spacing-right-medium:3.2%;--awb-spacing-left-medium:3.2%;--awb-width-small:100%;--awb-order-small:0;--awb-spacing-right-small:1.92%;--awb-spacing-left-small:1.92%;\"><div class=\"fusion-column-wrapper fusion-column-has-shadow fusion-flex-justify-content-flex-start fusion-content-layout-column\"><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-6\" style=\"--awb-font-size:30px;--awb-text-color:var(--awb-custom_color_3);\"><p>Training programs<\/p>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-7\" style=\"--awb-margin-top:20px;\"><p>The training opportunities at Giridhar Eye Institute are divided into Fellowships and Observerships. Fellowships involve direct clinical responsibility for patient care, both as outpatients and during surgery under supervision. Observers have no clinical responsibility and can only watch consultations without direct involvement in surgeries. GEI offers long-term fellowships lasting 12 to 24 months and short-term fellowships of 2 months. Observerships are one month long. Long-term programs are for young doctors seeking extensive practical training, while short-term programs are for practicing ophthalmologists wanting specialized experience in specific procedures.<\/p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-fullwidth fullwidth-box fusion-builder-row-5 fusion-flex-container has-pattern-background has-mask-background nonhundred-percent-fullwidth non-hundred-percent-height-scrolling fusion-no-medium-visibility fusion-no-large-visibility\" style=\"--awb-border-radius-top-left:0px;--awb-border-radius-top-right:0px;--awb-border-radius-bottom-right:0px;--awb-border-radius-bottom-left:0px;--awb-padding-top:60px;--awb-padding-bottom:60px;--awb-flex-wrap:wrap;\" ><div class=\"fusion-builder-row fusion-row fusion-flex-align-items-center fusion-flex-content-wrap\" style=\"max-width:1414.4px;margin-left: calc(-4% \/ 2 );margin-right: calc(-4% \/ 2 );\"><div class=\"fusion-layout-column fusion_builder_column fusion-builder-column-8 fusion_builder_column_2_5 2_5 fusion-flex-column\" style=\"--awb-bg-size:cover;--awb-width-large:40%;--awb-margin-top-large:0px;--awb-spacing-right-large:4.8%;--awb-margin-bottom-large:20px;--awb-spacing-left-large:4.8%;--awb-width-medium:40%;--awb-order-medium:0;--awb-spacing-right-medium:4.8%;--awb-spacing-left-medium:4.8%;--awb-width-small:100%;--awb-order-small:0;--awb-spacing-right-small:1.92%;--awb-spacing-left-small:1.92%;\"><div class=\"fusion-column-wrapper fusion-column-has-shadow fusion-flex-justify-content-flex-start fusion-content-layout-column\"><div class=\"fusion-image-element \" style=\"--awb-aspect-ratio:16 \/ 9;--awb-caption-title-font-family:var(--h2_typography-font-family);--awb-caption-title-font-weight:var(--h2_typography-font-weight);--awb-caption-title-font-style:var(--h2_typography-font-style);--awb-caption-title-size:var(--h2_typography-font-size);--awb-caption-title-transform:var(--h2_typography-text-transform);--awb-ca